  "response": "Records, specifically vinyl records, are primarily made of polyvinyl chloride (PVC), a type of plastic. The manufacturing process involves heating the PVC until it becomes a liquid, then pressing it into a mold with the record's grooves. Other materials can be added to the PVC to alter the record's properties, such as carbon to improve sound quality or different colors for aesthetic purposes.",
